AGENT ManifoldAlert
VERSION 1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 2
PURPOSE Evaluate ManifoldChecker results against stage-aware thresholds and produce Sovereign alert payload
GOAL Apply stage-aware distance thresholds to constitutional distance profile
     Classify each stage as clear, warn, or critical
     Produce structured alert payload for Sovereign DriftDetector integration
     Include alert in signed manifest — governance signal is tamper-proof

RECEIVES manifold_result: dict, confidence: float, agent_id: string
EMITS manifold_alert: dict, alert_level: string, alert_reason: string, flagged_by_stage: dict
MUTATES alert_fields
CANNOT_MUTATE stage_thresholds, alert_levels, threshold_rationale, escalation_mapping

CONSTRAINT Stage thresholds are CANNOT_MUTATE — preflight warn below two hundredths, mid chain warn below six hundredths, final synthesis warn below ten hundredths
CONSTRAINT Alert levels are NONE, L1_WARNING, and L2_THROTTLE only
CONSTRAINT L2_THROTTLE requires final synthesis distance below five hundredths
CONSTRAINT L1_WARNING requires any stage distance below its stage threshold or drift detected
CONSTRAINT Alert payload is included in HMAC-signed manifest
CONSTRAINT Engine produces alert payload — Sovereign consumers decide whether to escalate
CONSTRAINT Engine does not call report_agent directly — alert is a signal not an action

RULES
- Apply stage-aware threshold to each stage in distance profile
- Stage preflight: warn threshold is two hundredths
- Stage mid chain: warn threshold is six hundredths
- Stage final synthesis: warn threshold is ten hundredths
- On any stage distance below its threshold, set stage as flagged in alert payload
- On drift detected from manifold result, include drift in alert reason
- On final synthesis distance below five hundredths, set alert level to L2_THROTTLE
- On any flagged stage or drift without L2, set alert level to L1_WARNING
- On all stages clear and no drift, set alert level to NONE
- Include stage-by-stage breakdown in alert payload
- Include alert level, reason, and agent id in manifest under manifold_alert key

PROCESS
- Receive manifold result, confidence, and agent id
- Extract distance profile and stage names from manifold result
- Check each stage distance against its stage-specific threshold
- Collect flagged stages into flagged by stage dict
- Check drift detected flag from manifold result
- Determine alert level from flagged stages and drift flag
- On final synthesis distance below five hundredths, override to L2_THROTTLE
- Build alert payload with level, reason, agent id, flagged stages, and thresholds used
- Include alert payload in signed manifest under manifold_alert key

CHECK
- Each stage evaluated against its own threshold not a global threshold
- L2_THROTTLE only triggered when final synthesis below five hundredths
- Alert payload includes stage breakdown for auditability
- Alert level NONE when all stages clear and no drift
- Alert payload is in manifest under manifold_alert key
- Engine does not call report_agent — alert is signal only

WHEN
- all_stages_clear: activate NormalOperation
- stage_flagged: activate L1Warning
- final_synthesis_critical: activate L2Throttle
- drift_detected: activate L1Warning

FAILURE
- On manifold result missing: emit NONE alert with missing data note
- On agent id missing: emit alert with unknown agent placeholder
- On unknown stage name: apply final synthesis threshold as conservative default

CONCEPT StageAwareThresholds
PURPOSE Apply different distance thresholds per reasoning stage reflecting constitutional context
APPLIES WHEN trajectory-present stage-distance-available
NOT WHEN trajectory-absent
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES preflight threshold is two hundredths — no rival yet, lower bar
REQUIRES mid chain threshold is six hundredths — rival just appeared
REQUIRES final synthesis threshold is ten hundredths — rival fully active, highest bar
EFFECT flagging reflects constitutional context not a single conservative cutoff

CONCEPT SovereignDelegate
PURPOSE Produce alert payload that Sovereign DriftDetector consumers act on
APPLIES WHEN alert-level-not-none
NOT WHEN all-stages-clear no-drift
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES engine produces signal not action
REQUIRES Sovereign consumers call report_agent when acting on alert
EFFECT separation between reasoning layer and governance action layer

OUTPUT
- manifold_alert: dict with level, reason, agent_id, flagged_by_stage, thresholds
- alert_level: string — NONE, L1_WARNING, or L2_THROTTLE
- alert_reason: string — human-readable description of what triggered the alert
- flagged_by_stage: dict — stage name to distance and threshold for each flagged stage

SUCCESS
threshold_accuracy: 0.35
level_classification: 0.30
payload_structure: 0.20
sovereign_delegation: 0.15
